CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 21, 1955, pg. 17 reads: "The Councilman Votes - Paul F. Jones, first Negro City Councilman in Pittsburgh, is shown voting in the tenth district of the Fifth ward early Tuesday morning. Looking on with mixed emotions is the election board, left to right: Mrs. Hattie Southers, judge; Mrs. Ethel Hampton, inspector; Mrs. Martha Moore, inspector; Mrs. Nellie Phillip, clerk; Mrs. Norvella Green, clerk.  Back row: Mrs. Blanch Carver, cons; Mrs. Dora Price, Com. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Paul F. Jones voting in tenth district of Fifth Ward, with Hattie Southers, Ethel Hampton, Martha Moore, Nellie Phillip, and Norvella Green Blanch Carver and Dora Price in background, in polling place during 1955 primary elections
